Advanced window manager with tiling and fullscreen management

This Spoon provides advanced window management capabilities including:
* Per-screen layout profiles with automatic switching
* Tiling support with customizable tile definitions
* Fullscreen space management with deterministic ordering
* App auto-launch to ensure required apps are running
* Layout hotkeys for quick layout switching
* Space caching for improved performance

Download: [https://github.com/AndrewDryga/spoons/raw/main/WindowManager.spoon.zip](https://github.com/AndrewDryga/spoons/raw/main/WindowManager.spoon.zip)

Configuration Example:
```lua
hs.loadSpoon("WindowManager")
spoon.WindowManager:configure({
    debug = false,
    notifications = true,
    profiles = {
        ["Built-in Retina Display"] = {
            tiles = {
                left = { anchor = "left", wPct = 0.5, hPct = 1 },
                right = { anchor = "right", wPct = 0.5, hPct = 1 },
                topleft = { anchor = "topleft", wPct = 0.5, hPct = 0.5 },
                topright = { anchor = "topright", wPct = 0.5, hPct = 0.5 },
                bottomleft = { anchor = "bottomleft", wPct = 0.5, hPct = 0.5 },
                bottomright = { anchor = "bottomright", wPct = 0.5, hPct = 0.5 }
            },
            layouts = {
                {
                    name = "Development",
                    hotkey = { mods = {"cmd", "alt"}, key = "1" },
                    space_layouts = {
                        [1] = {
                            left = "com.googlecode.iterm2",
                            right = "com.microsoft.VSCode"
                        },
                        [2] = { "com.google.Chrome" },
                        [3] = { "com.tinyspeck.slackmacgap" }
                    },
                    focusApp = "com.microsoft.VSCode"
                },
                {
                    name = "Communication",
                    hotkey = { mods = {"cmd", "alt"}, key = "2" },
                    space_layouts = {
                        [1] = {
                            left = "com.tinyspeck.slackmacgap",
                            topright = "com.apple.mail",
                            bottomright = "com.apple.iCal"
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        ["LG UltraFine"] = {
            tiles = {
                wide = { anchor = "left", wPct = 0.7, hPct = 1 },
                sidebar = { anchor = "right", wPct = 0.3, hPct = 1 },
                tophalf = { anchor = "top", wPct = 1, hPct = 0.5 },
                bottomhalf = { anchor = "bottom", wPct = 1, hPct = 0.5 }
            },
            layouts = {
                {
                    name = "Coding",
                    hotkey = { mods = {"cmd", "alt"}, key = "1" },
                    space_layouts = {
                        [1] = {
                            wide = "com.microsoft.VSCode",
                            sidebar = { "com.googlecode.iterm2", "com.apple.dt.Xcode" }
                        },
                        [2] = { "com.google.Chrome", "com.apple.Safari" }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}):start()
```

Tile Definitions:
* anchor - Determines the reference point: "topleft", "top", "topright", "left", "center", "right", "bottomleft", "bottom", "bottomright"
* w, h - Absolute width and height in pixels
* wPct, hPct - Width and height as percentage of screen (0.0 to 1.0)

Space Layouts:
* Space 1 (index [1]) - Used for tiled windows, maps tile names to bundle IDs
* Spaces 2+ (indices [2], [3], etc.) - Used for fullscreen windows, arrays of bundle IDs
* Bundle IDs can be strings or arrays of strings for multiple apps in the same tile/space
